'''''dol''''' in [[Sindarin]] means "head" and also poetically "hill" instead of ''[[amon]]''.<ref>{{S|Appendix}}, ''dol''</ref>

==Etymology==
From [[OS]] *''dola'', [[PQ]] [[Sundocarmë|Root]] [[NDOL]]<ref>{{LR|Etymologies}}, '''NDOL'''</ref>

*''[[Dol Baran#Etymology|'''Dol''' Baran]]''
*''[[Dol Guldur#Etymology|'''Dol''' Guldur]]''
*''[[Dolmed#Etymology|'''Dol'''med]]''
*''[[Mindolluin#Etymology|Min'''dol'''luin]]''
*''[[Nardol#Etymology|Nar'''dol''']]''
*''[[Fanuidhol#Etymology|Fanui'''dhol''']]''

==Cognates==
*[[Quenya]] ''[[nóla]]''
*Sindarin ''[[amon]]''

==Other versions==
The [[Noldorin]] version is given as ''dôl''.
